  local int checksum;

  function void calc_checksum();
    checksum = 100;

  endfunction

  function int get_checksum();
    return checksum;
  endfunction
endclass

Packet p = new();
// p.checksum = 10;   âŒ ERROR (not accessible)
```

âœ” Only methods inside `Packet` can access `checksum`.

---

## ğŸ”¹ 2. `protected` Access Modifier

### âœ… Meaning:

* Accessible:

  * Inside the **same class**
  * Inside **child (derived) classes**
* âŒ Not accessible from outside objects

### ğŸ“Œ Use when:

You want **inheritance support**, but still want protection from outside access.

### âœ… Example:

```systemverilog
class Packet;
  protected int size;

  function void set_size(int s);
    size = s;
  endfunction
endclass

class ExtPacket extends Packet;
  function void display();
    $display("Size = %0d", size);  // âœ… Allowed
  endfunction
endclass

Packet p = new();
// p.size = 10;  âŒ ERROR
```

âœ” Child class can access
âŒ External access not allowed

