Yes âœ… â€” **you *can* use `local` and `protected` with methods (functions/tasks)** in SystemVerilog.

But there are **rules and limitations**, so letâ€™s make it very clear.

---

## âœ… Short Answer

| Modifier    | Can be used on methods? | Meaning                               |
| ----------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `local`     | âœ… Yes                   | Only accessible inside the same class |
| `protected` | âœ… Yes                   | Accessible in class + child classes   |
| (default)   | âœ… Yes                   | Public â€“ accessible everywhere        |

---

## ğŸ”¹ Example: `local` Method

```systemverilog
